soc.message

Class SOCNewGameWithOptions

  • java.lang.Object
    • soc.message.SOCMessage
      • soc.message.SOCMessageTemplate2s
        • soc.message.SOCNewGameWithOptions
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, SOCMessageForGame

    public class SOCNewGameWithOptions
extends SOCMessageTemplate2s
    This broadcast message from server announces a new game, with a certain version and possibly game options, to all clients.
    • This message is followed by JOINGAMEAUTH to the requesting client, so they will join the game they just created.
    Introduced in 1.1.07; check server version against VERSION_FOR_NEWGAMEWITHOPTIONS before sending this message.

    Game name may include a prefix marker if the client can't join; see SOCGames.MARKER_THIS_GAME_UNJOINABLE. This marker will be retained within the game name returned by SOCMessageTemplate2s.getGame().

    Just like NEWGAME, robot clients don't need to handle this message type. Bots ignore new-game announcements and are asked to join specific games.

    Since:
    1.1.07
    Author:
    Jeremy D. Monin <jeremy@nand.net>

    • Constructor Detail

      • SOCNewGameWithOptions

        public SOCNewGameWithOptions(SOCGame ga,
                             int cliVers)
        Create a SOCNewGameWithOptions message at server, to send to a specific client version. Game otions and minimum required version will be extracted from ga.

        Before v2.4.50 this constructor was a static toCmd(..) method.

        Parameters:
        ga - the game; will call SOCGame.getGameOptions()
        cliVers - Client version; assumed >= VERSION_FOR_NEWGAMEWITHOPTIONS. If any game's options need adjustment for an older client, cliVers triggers that. Use -2 if the client version doesn't matter.
        Since:
        2.4.50

      • SOCNewGameWithOptions

        public SOCNewGameWithOptions(java.lang.String ga,
                             SOCGameOptionSet opts,
                             int minVers,
                             int cliVers)
        Create a SOCNewGameWithOptions message, optionally for a specific client version, at server. This constructor may adjust encoded option values for backwards compatibility with the client version. If so, contents of the referenced opts map aren't changed: Calls SOCGameOption.packOptionsToString(opts, false, false, cliVers).
        Parameters:
        ga - the name of the game; the game name may have the SOCGames.MARKER_THIS_GAME_UNJOINABLE prefix.
        opts - Requested game options, as a read-only map
        minVers - Minimum client version required for this game, or -1
        cliVers - Client version, if any game's options need adjustment for an older client. Use -2 if the client version doesn't matter, or if adjustment should not be done.
        Since:
        2.0.00
